Fijians refer to the word ‘chimoango’ to refer to Christians. This word is derived from English and cannot be discerned in the Fijian language as ‘kokonut’ has been.

So if you are ever accused by a Christian in Fiji of being a kokonut find yourself a new church!

God opposes the proud, But gives grace to the humble. Thus, humble yourselves under the mighty hand of God, that He may exalt you in due time, casting all your care upon Him, for He cares for you. Have a peaceful Sunday. Grace and peace to you.

Dennis & Judy Lucks- HFAN Directors

Ever wondered just how tall the serpent was? Serpents normally grow 5 to 6 feet long, and my guess here is that during that period of time they can grow a total of over 30 feet. Environmental conditions can vary from no cool winters to maybe a month (tops) of cool weather. Then during the long summer days they can grow 45 centimetres a week, they can double their length in less than three months!
